nch   Bourgeois  .","History: Thomas Burgess came from England to MA <i>c.</i> 1630 and eventually settled in Sandwich, MA."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anne de Bruges Herit. Gruuthuyse was born about 1287, in Europe, her father, Jean de Bruges, was 24 and her mother, Marguerite de Ghistelles, was 22. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Gerhard van Der Aa. She died in 1344, at the age of 58."},"et":{"about 1287–1344":"umbes 1287–1344","1287–1344":"1287–1344","1287–1327":"1287–1327","1313–1360":"1313–1360","1320–Female":"1320–Surnud","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1327":"1327","1313":"1313","1344":"1344","1267":"1267","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","1287":"1287","Abt 1313":"umbes 1313","1360":"1360","um 1327":"umbes 1327","about 1287":"umbes 1287","Europe":"Europe"},"fi":{"about 1287–1344":"noin 1287–1344","1287–1344":"1287–1344","1287–1327":"1287–1327","1313–1360":"1313–1360","1320–Female":"1320–Kuollut","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","1327":"1327","1313":"1313","1344":"1344","1267":"1267","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","1287":"1287","Abt 1313":"noin 1313","1360":"1360","um 1327":"noin 1327","about 1287":"noin 1287","Europe":"Europe"},"fr":{"about 1287–1344":"environ 1287–1344","1287–1344":"1287–1344"